# PA-GFP F153A Cavity Engineering Script
# Author: Shen Khaw
# Project: Computational Prediction of Steric Cavities in PA-GFP

# 1. Initialize and Load Structure
reinitialize
# Load the specific baseline file you saved
load t203h_baseline.pdb, pagfp

# 2. Basic Visualization Setup
hide everything, pagfp
show cartoon, pagfp
show sticks, resn CHR  # Show the chromophore in stick representation

# 3. Establish Baseline (T203H)
# Measure baseline distance to chromophore 
distance baseline_dist, /pagfp//A/203/CA, /pagfp//A/CHR/CA
# Expected result: ~3.3 Å

# 4. Engineer Novel F153A Mutation
wizard mutagenesis
mutagenesis 153, ALA
# (Note: In the GUI, select the best rotamer to minimize clashes, then apply)
apply
wizard 0

# 5. Measure Mutant Distance to Chromophore
distance mutant_dist, /pagfp//A/153/CA, /pagfp//A/CHR/CA
# Expected result: ~13.3 Å (Expanded cavity)

# 6. Visualize the Cavity and Steric Environment
# Show the mutated residue in sticks to see the new empty space
show sticks, resi 153
color yellow, resi 153

# 7. Save the Final Mutated Structure
save F153A_PA-GFP_Mutant.pdb, pagfp

# 8. Render a high-quality image for the paper
ray 1200, 1200
png F153A_Cavity_Visualization.png
